## 7. LOD LAYERS APPROACH (TASK-023: 31 entries)

### 7.1 Four LOD Levels

| Level | Zoom | View | Granularity |
|-------|------|------|-------------|
| MACRO/Strategic | < 0.3x | Heatmap | Years (10-12 year overview) |
| MESO/Tactical | 0.3-1.0x | DNA Bars | Quarters/Months |
| OPERATIONAL | 1.0-3.0x | DNA Gantt | Weeks/Months |
| MICRO/Execution | > 3.0x | Task Cards | Days |

### 7.2 Visual Implementations

**Heatmap (MACRO):**
- Yellow → Orange → Red gradient (utilization)
- Quarterly cells (6,144 = 128 trains × 48 quarters)
- Purple/orange for overhauls

**DNA Bars (MESO):**
- Blue (maintenance), Orange (overhaul), Gray (inspection), Red (conflict)
- Horizontal strips resembling DNA sequence
- Train rows with colored blocks

**Task Cards (MICRO):**
- Task names, status badges, date ranges
- Progress bars, resource indicators
- Dependency lines with arrows
- Conflict warning icons

### 7.3 Transition System

- **Hermite smoothstep** for opacity crossfade
- **CROSSFADE_RANGE** for smooth blend zones
- Example: At 0.34x → Strategic 30%, Tactical 70%

```javascript
const smoothStep = (value, edge0, edge1) => {
  const t = Math.max(0, Math.min(1, (value - edge0) / (edge1 - edge0)));
  return t * t * (3 - 2 * t);
};
```

### 7.4 Performance

- **Achieved:** 120-123 FPS average across all LOD levels
- **Target:** 60K tasks @ 60fps
- **Techniques:**
  - RBush spatial indexing (~1.6-2.9ms for ~5000 items)
  - InstancedMesh with vertexColors
  - LTTB downsampling (97.7% reduction, 43.8x compression)
  - DataFilterExtension for GPU-based filtering

